575d4c3f2cf3d6dc3ed83148.description:
Neuralquest


Experimental: Neuralquest is an experimental application. Feel free to look around. We are currently not accepting new users.

What

Neualquest is a platform that helps people organize and work together.

As a visitor you can browse published information.

As a user you have your own space in which you can maintain blogs, photo albums, create your own apps etc. and publish them as desired. Users can send messages and engage in agreements that for example, triggers a process that result in the purchase of an item on offer.

Uses can also take part in or create organizations based on industry standard templates, which can then evolve as the need arises. Role based authorization ensures that only members of your organization assigned to a particular organizational unit can read/modify data.

Why

The IT industry has been notably lacking when it come to support for business processes. Today, a typical large organization might have hundreds of systems running on thousands of servers. Each of these systems requires a small army of experts just to keep it from falling over. This complexity comes at huge expense.

Why don't we have a single system that regards the entire business as a single process? Any CIO will tell you No one system can deliver the flexibility and robustness required to meet our ever evolving business needs and if it did, licencing fees would soon cost us an arm and a leg.

Neuralquest disputes this supposition. We say: By taking a different approach to how we do IT, it is possible to be both flexible and robust with a single system. The open source nature of the project ensures we avoid vendor lock-in and can rely on a vast support community.

How

Neuralquest is really three things:

  • An open source project, maintained on GitHub.
  • The Standard Model: A baseline model consisting of classes and objects needed to do basic business processes.
  • A cloud service in which we demonstrate the possibilities that Neuralquest offers. Free for noncommercial use.

The key selling point of Neuralquest is flexibility and robustness at minimal costs, meaning: easy to install, use, maintain, learn, adapt etc.  Flexibility is achieved by:

  • Death to 3GL: No programming, only modeling
  • Fully self documenting through dozens of overviews and diagrams.
  • A minimalist architecture involving a single collection as data store and an extremely small code base: just 6k lines of code means bugs are ironed out quickly.

Robustness is achieved by implementing internet standard: TODO.

Best of all: it's free.

575d4c3f2cf3d6dc3ed83151.description:
The question Neuralquest set out to answer is:

What is the least amount of complexity it takes to do business processes?

Complexity is important because this is where all the money goes. Keeping a system simple offers exponential benefits in terms of running costs, maintenance, learning curve, extensibility, support and vulnerability.
Our focus is on business processes because that where the money comes from. Perhaps more importantly, business processes contain all the "hard bits"

582e3f25425310133a49f105.description:
A Standard Model is provided which includes all the classes/objects and their associations needed to do basic business processes.

Exstensible: If you're working standalone you can extend the model to your heart's delight.

Several diagrams provide insight into the inner workings of the Standard Model.
582e3f25425310133a49f105.name: Class Model

582e3f51425310133a49f107.description:
Users can initiate agreements with other users/organizations to transfer ownership of resources or provide services.

Finite state machine: Each agreement progresses through a hierarchy of potential states, until it is closed.

Role-based authorization: Each state correspondes to a view which only a member of your organization, with a particular role can access.

Workbasket: Each user is provided with a list of agreements that require his/her attention, based on his/her roles in organizations.

A set of template organizations is provided that you can copy to create your own organizations.

Audit Trail, Imutable Agreements, Blockchain?
582e3f51425310133a49f107.name: Process Model

582e4dea425310133a49f109.description:
Large organizations typicly employ hundreds of loosely coupled systems. Each of these systems requires a small army of experts to keep it from falling over. Valnerability increases exponetially with each system in the chain. These systems communicate with each other though interfaces. Everytime you copy data or send a message:

  • Send individual messages or filebasedt Lag time: acceptable? 
  • How do systems respond if a sent message is not recieved? 
  • Does it even know? 
  • You might have multiple feeds. 
  • What if feeds conflict? 
  • Update is missed or has already taken place: acceptable? 
  • Reconcilliation: which direction? how often? how to deal with exceptions? who is right? 
  • How to deal with duplicates: funtional merge?
  • Authorization, authentication, encryption, key stores, firewalls, network performancet 
Organizations avoid syncronous transactions because they require each and every component to support syncronous behaviour. Developing, documenting, managing the interfaces in a large organization represents a huge undertaking and is often done poorly. Systems will have diffrent retention/auditing requirments
In short: Copying data is a really bad idea. tIt leads to deterioration of data quality and excessive maintance costs, and yet we do it all the time.
Why not a single data store? It was once thought that Relational Database Managers would take on this role. It was not to be. Today, each system comes with it own database. tDirect connection to foreign databases is frowned upon, with good reason. tAll the above issues can be avoided if we resort to a single data store
582e4dea425310133a49f109.name: Complextity

5834a357ef13367319ef0b3c.description:
The Page Model consists of a heirarchy of pages and subpages that can be used to navigate the data-graph, following parent-child relationships.

Pages can have Tabs or Accordions to present various aspects of a parent object.

Tabs can be populated with various types of widgets: Tree, Table, Form, Document, Charts etc.

The URL can be bookmarked. The same page set will be created with recent data.

A set of published pages are provided that you can reuse in your own Page Model.
